The basic course of cartography will provide the principles of map making and cartographic presentation, as well as map projections and issues of digital cartography. Students will compile and design a small thematic map during a laboratoryObjectives/eesmärkid:  This basic course of cartography will provide the principles of map making and cartographic presentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful passing the student: - will understand the basic concepts of cartography and is able to explain them; - will understand the character of communication in cartography; - will understand the basic of map projections; - will understand the process of map production; - knows principles of cartographic design and symbolization; - is able to generalize a map; - will understand how to add text to a map; - knows principles of color theory; - knows principles of map reproduction; - has an overview of the cartographic activities in Estonia.
